{
  "texts": [
    "Secondly, we emphasize whether the data captures genuine emotions or acted/imitated emotions.",
    "Genuine emotions are preferred to ensure the authenticity and real-life accuracy of the trained recognition model.",
    "Lastly, the choice of target labels determines the dataset's suitability for a specific use case.",
    "A significant distinction exists between datasets employing continuous models (valence/arousal) and those using discrete emotion models.",
    "The count of categories for discrete emotions varies widely, ranging from 3 to 26."
  ]
}